def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    index = data.index

    clocs = [index._get_level_number(i) for i in clocs]

    ull = data[clocs]

    if len(clocs) == 2 and isinstance(data.columns, MultiIndex):
        result = data
        for i in range(len(clocs)):
            val = clocs[i]
            result = result.unstack(val, fill_value=fill_value)
            clocs = [v if i > v else v - 1 for v in clocs]

        return result

    # Reorganize the columns
    levels = data.columns.levels
    codes = data.columns.codes
    names = data.columns.names
    new_codes = []
    for c in clocs:
        new_codes.append(codes[c])
    new_columns = MultiIndex.from_product([levels[i] for i in clocs], names=[names[i] for i in clocs])
    
    unstacked = data.unstack(clocs, fill_value=fill_value)
    unstacked.columns = new_columns

    return unstacked
